Create folder name Project Agumentation 
Project Agumentation/
│── Attendance.csv
│── encode_student.py
│── face_recognition.py
│
├── Students/
│     ├── student1.jpg
│     ├── student2.jpg
│     └── ... (all student images)
│
└── logo/
      └── logo.png
Step 1: Create Main Project Folder
Create a folder named:
Project Agumentation

Step 2: Place Main Files Inside
Inside Project Agumentation, store the following three files:
Attendance.csv
encode_student.py
face_recognition.py

Step 3: Create Subfolders
Inside Project Agumentation, create two additional folders:
Students/ → Store all student images here.
logo/ → Store your logo image here.

Step 4: Update File Paths in Code
In both encode_student.py and face_recognition.py, make sure all paths match this folder structure. Or your own folder structure. 
